# CODEOWNERS — who gets auto-requested for review on a pull request.
#
# HOW IT WORKS
#   • When a PR changes a file, the owners matched below are automatically
#     added as reviewers.
#   • Ownership is enforced ONLY if branch protection on `main` has
#     "Require review from Code Owners" enabled. It is currently OFF
#     (required approvals = 0), so these lines just auto-request reviewers
#     and don't block merges yet. Turn it on in:
#     Settings → Branches → main → Require review from Code Owners.
#
# SYNTAX
#   • <pattern>  <owner> [<owner>…]   — gitignore-style glob, then owners.
#   • Owners are @user, @org/team, or email addresses.
#   • LAST matching pattern wins (opposite of .gitignore). Put broad rules
#     first, specific overrides later.
#   • Valid locations (first found wins): .github/CODEOWNERS, /CODEOWNERS,
#     docs/CODEOWNERS.
#
# Replace @tekrogen below with the right user/team once collaborators join.

# ── Default owner for everything ────────────────────────────────────────
*                       @tekrogen

# ── Vendored Design System registry ─────────────────────────────────────
# These are vendored from Tekrogen-Brand-Design-System and must NOT be
# edited here — fix upstream in the DS repo and re-vendor (see CLAUDE.md).
# Flagging them routes any accidental change to a reviewer.
/components/             @tekrogen

# ── Token layer (kept at DS parity) ─────────────────────────────────────
colors_and_type.css      @tekrogen
/scripts/palette.js      @tekrogen

# ── Mockup surfaces & build briefs ──────────────────────────────────────
/index.html              @tekrogen
/mockups/                @tekrogen

# ── Governance, CI, and project config ──────────────────────────────────
/.github/                @tekrogen
/CLAUDE.md               @tekrogen
/release-please-config.json        @tekrogen
/.release-please-manifest.json     @tekrogen
